  "body": "#### System information\n\n```\nGeth\nVersion: 1.4.17-stable-5a6008e0\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\nNetwork Id: 1\nGo Version: go1.5.1\nOS: linux\nGOPATH=\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go\n```\n\ni have attached below a zip with several log files where geth sometimes just quits silently, or reports a backtrace, sometimes complaining about memory.\n\nit first happened while i was doing a --fast sync, and now regularly that i'm continuing the sync.\n\nmy machine has 4GB, 2GB is used for geth cache, and geth is alone on the linux.\n\nthis is how i start geth:\n\n```\n#!/bin/bash\n\nSCRIPT_DIR=`dirname \"$0\"`\nSCRIPT_DIR=`readlink -f ${SCRIPT_DIR}`\n\npushd \"${SCRIPT_DIR}\"\n\nwhile true; do\n  now=\"`date +%Y-%m-%d-%H:%M:%S`\"\n  ./go-ethereum/build/bin/geth --oppose-dao-fork --jspath \"${SCRIPT_DIR}\" --preload \"geth-autoload.js\" --nat any --cache 2048 --rpc --rpccorsdomain localhost 2>&1 | tee /var/log/geth/geth-${now}.log\n\n  echo \"looping to restart geth...\"\n  sleep 1\ndone\n\npopd\n```\n#### Backtrace\n\n[geth-crash-logs.zip](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/files/527571/geth-crash-logs.zip)\n",
